00:07:16.699 --> 00:07:17.699
the Draw Pattern.

00:07:17.699 --> 00:07:18.699
And I'm pretty

00:07:18.699 --> 00:07:20.749
sure they're aware that this isn't quite the
right Draw Pattern, but I wanted to put it

00:07:20.749 --> 00:07:22.129
out there for other people who

00:07:22.129 --> 00:07:23.129
may be watching.

00:07:23.129 --> 00:07:24.129
&gt;&gt;Ian: Yeah.

00:07:24.129 --> 00:07:29.259
&gt;&gt;Reto: So, this is following that prototype
G+ model where the action bar all shifts across

00:07:29.259 --> 00:07:30.270
and you can see that here.

00:07:30.270 --> 00:07:32.159
So, everything's moved across.

00:07:32.159 --> 00:07:35.849
The right model is actually the way YouTube
does it, which is that your action bar is

00:07:35.849 --> 00:07:36.909
consistent.

00:07:36.909 --> 00:07:40.860
So all of the--oops--all the stuff here along
your action bar, this should stay here no

00:07:40.860 --> 00:07:41.860
matter what.

00:07:41.860 --> 00:07:42.860
And

00:07:42.860 --> 00:07:46.949
rather than having a draw icon, you would
have your application icon or logo with an

00:07:46.949 --> 00:07:48.090
up affordance.

00:07:48.090 --> 00:07:49.090
So then, clicking

00:07:49.090 --> 00:07:53.189
that will then leave everything here as it
is and then just have this side part here

00:07:53.189 --> 00:07:54.189
slide out.

00:07:54.189 --> 00:07:55.189
So in the same way, but

00:07:55.189 --> 00:07:58.039
still having the action bar along the top.

00:07:58.039 --> 00:07:59.921
And I think, so that's the right way to do
it.

00:07:59.921 --> 00:08:00.921
And that's all listed in the

00:08:00.921 --> 00:08:02.949
design patterns on Android design.

00:08:02.949 --> 00:08:03.949
&gt;&gt;Ian: Yeah.

