the reason why this is particularly important

00:48:18.700 --> 00:48:24.359
for cameras is because there was an assumption
at the very, very, very early days of Android

00:48:24.359 --> 00:48:28.609
that every device would have a camera as part
of the compatibility test sweep.

00:48:28.609 --> 00:48:34.739
And since that has gradually relaxed over
time to give more opportunities for differences

00:48:34.739 --> 00:48:40.300
in hardware, we have had to maintain that
assumption that if you are asking for a camera

00:48:40.300 --> 00:48:44.319
permission, that must mean you need a camera
for the device.

00:48:44.319 --> 00:48:45.880
And that’s no longer the case.

00:48:45.880 --> 00:48:50.359
And so you have to explicitly say hey, I know
that I've asked for the permission to use

00:48:50.359 --> 00:48:53.559
the camera, but even if the camera isn't there,
that’s fine I'm still happy to run.

00:48:53.559 --> 00:48:59.049
